comment: Agree
commentable_entity.ask: Please grant Johnny Depp his appeal.
commentable_entity.title: Ministry of Justice: Grant Johnny Depp his appeal.
commentable_entity.description:
On the 2nd of November 2020 a travesty of justice occurred. John Cristopher Depp II had mountains of evidence dismissed, specialist police testimony and medical notes disregarded and independent witness ignored.
All of the evidence is available for any member of the public to see and we have! We have read court documents, statements and we have heard the audio recordings of Amber Laura Heard gaslighting, intimidating and dosing up her victim, we have heard her admitting to the abusing him. We have seen moving and disappearing bruises.
Our justice system is being questioned all over the world. We have lost faith.
Now whilst trying to spread the truth we are being attacked in the media as crazed ‘Fans’ who are threatening her. We are not, we just want justice. Abuse has no gender.
We are supporters, we are fans but the vast majority are abuse survivors who have been shocked and appalled by this verdict and his continued abuse in the media.
We say enough is enough, please hear our voices and grant Johnny Depp the appeal and justice he deserves
commentable_entity.letter_body: Please grant Johnny Depp his appeal.

comment:
Ms Heard claimed to have donated millions of her divorce settlement to two charities. Subsequent court proceedings indicate that years later they have not received any donations from her. Charities rely on people making good on their pledge so that they can help those that are less fortunate. She pledged $3.5m to each charity, a total of $7m.

- I will no longer support any charity or cause Ms Heard is an ambassador of. (Apologies to the charities but you will need to find more appropriate advocates or ambassadors).

- I will no longer buy or support any product Ms Heard is promoting, paid or otherwise. Including employment in any capacity she has in any aspect within the media, particularly the movie industry.

On the 2nd of November 2020 a travesty of justice occurred. John Cristopher Depp II had mountains of evidence dismissed, specialist police testimony and medical notes disregarded and independent witness ignored.
All of the evidence is available for any member of the public to see and we have! We have read court documents, statements and we have heard the audio recordings of Amber Laura Heard gaslighting, intimidating and dosing up her victim, we have heard her admitting to the abusing him. We have seen moving and disappearing bruises.
Our justice system is being questioned all over the world. We have lost faith.
Now whilst trying to spread the truth we are being attacked in the media as crazed ‘Fans’ who are threatening her. We are not, we just want justice. Abuse has no gender.
We are supporters, we are fans but the vast majority are abuse survivors who have been shocked and appalled by this verdict and his continued abuse in the media.
We say enough is enough, please hear our voices and grant Johnny Depp the appeal and justice he deserves
commentable_entity.letter_body: Please grant Johnny Depp his appeal.

All of the evidence is available for any member of the public to see and we have! We have read court documents, statements and we have heard the audio recordings of Amber Laura Heard gaslighting, intimidating and dosing up her victim, we have heard her admitting to the abusing him. We have seen moving and disappearing bruises.
Our justice system is being questioned all over the world. We have lost faith.
Now whilst trying to spread the truth we are being attacked in the media as crazed ‘Fans’ who are threatening her. We are not, we just want justice. Abuse has no gender.
We are supporters, we are fans but the vast majority are abuse survivors who have been shocked and appalled by this verdict and his continued abuse in the media.
We say enough is enough, please hear our voices and grant Johnny Depp the appeal and justice he deserves

comment: The judge preceeding the case (Justice Nicol) was clearly quite biased in his judgement. As some of us dug, we found that the judge has ties with Ms. Heard and the Sun’s editor Mr. Dan Wootton, as well as ties towards women’s movements through his wife. That in itself is a conflict of interest and he should of recused himself at the beginning of the trial, which he did not. The judge also based his ruling, not on the evidence provided, but on his personal assumptions. Through everything that he has gone through, Johnny Depp deserves the chance to have this cased ruled fairly and unbiasely. Please give him a chance!

commentable_entity.title: Ministry of Justice: Grant Johnny Depp his appeal.
commentable_entity.description:
On the 2nd of November 2020 a travesty of justice occurred. John Cristopher Depp II had mountains of evidence dismissed, specialist police testimony and medical notes disregarded and independent witness ignored.
All of the evidence is available for any member of the public to see and we have! We have read court documents, statements and we have heard the audio recordings of Amber Laura Heard gaslighting, intimidating and dosing up her victim, we have heard her admitting to the abusing him. We have seen moving and disappearing bruises.
Our justice system is being questioned all over the world. We have lost faith.
Now whilst trying to spread the truth we are being attacked in the media as crazed ‘Fans’ who are threatening her. We are not, we just want justice. Abuse has no gender.
We are supporters, we are fans but the vast majority are abuse survivors who have been shocked and appalled by this verdict and his continued abuse in the media.
We say enough is enough, please hear our voices and grant Johnny Depp the appeal and justice he deserves
commentable_entity.letter_body: Please grant Johnny Depp his appeal.

To this biased, paid-off judge who was already connected to both NGN's and Amber Heard's legal teams, the "word" of one woman outweighed the eyewitness statements of police officers, security guards, building and property staff members, doctors, nurses, housekeepers, personal assistants, and more who testified to Amber's abusive behaviour and lack of injuries, as well as Johnny's proven injuries from her... in addition to the undisputed evidence of audio recordings in which Amber admits to abusing Johnny and that he "runs away" from every fight/her abuse, CCTV footage which shows Amber uninjured and cheating on him, photos of Johnny's injuries, medical records of Johnny's injuries, text messages, and several points of contrast which debunk her claims. None of it was even mentioned in the judge's ruling, as if it was never presented at all. 

Justice Nicol was never worthy of this case, nor was he an appropriate or impartial choice. His prior connections to Murdoch, Jennifer Robinson, and their law firm (as well as Amber's fraternisation behind the scenes of this trial) made this entire process unethical. Justice was NOT served, and Johnny continues to be punished  and victim-blamed. He is owed this appeal under a court with a competent judge.

On the 2nd of November 2020 a travesty of justice occurred. John Cristopher Depp II had mountains of evidence dismissed, specialist police testimony and medical notes disregarded and independent witness ignored.
All of the evidence is available for any member of the public to see and we have! We have read court documents, statements and we have heard the audio recordings of Amber Laura Heard gaslighting, intimidating and dosing up her victim, we have heard her admitting to the abusing him. We have seen moving and disappearing bruises.
Our justice system is being questioned all over the world. We have lost faith.
Now whilst trying to spread the truth we are being attacked in the media as crazed ‘Fans’ who are threatening her. We are not, we just want justice. Abuse has no gender.
We are supporters, we are fans but the vast majority are abuse survivors who have been shocked and appalled by this verdict and his continued abuse in the media.
We say enough is enough, please hear our voices and grant Johnny Depp the appeal and justice he deserves
commentable_entity.letter_body: Please grant Johnny Depp his appeal.
